    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen the window that contains the terminal with nvim is not bigger than say , half of the screen.\r\nIt opens and looks correct, but as soon as you scroll you get weird graphical artifacts.\r\n\r\nIt only restores once you resize the window \r\n\r\n![20230703_13h19m14s_grim](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/17380530/087ccee5-f8e7-46aa-b7fc-fdb2e86f7c33)\r\n\r\n\r\n![20230703_13h19m31s_grim](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/17380530/30bc83dd-ae10-4924-9819-c229cede2bb8)\r\n\r\n![20230703_13h19m37s_grim](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/17380530/01044ad3-430f-44be-9ec4-f8de15fce407)\r\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nopen nvim on a terminal\r\nscroll down on the document\r\nIt stays on an infinite glitch until you resize\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNo glitch\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.9.1 Build type: Release LuaJIT 2.1.0-beta3\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux arch 6.3.9-arch1-1 #1 SMP PREEMPT_DYNAMIC Wed, 21 Jun 2023 20:46:20 +0000 x86_64 GNU/Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty 0.12.2 (9d9982df) , kitty 0.28.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacritty\n\n### Installation\n\npacman",
